  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Pat the <strong>pork belly</strong>&nbsp;dry and rub&nbsp;it all over with a generous amount of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a dry pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat and, once hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat-side down and cook for 5 min, then flip and cook for a further 2 min until coloured</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the coloured <strong>pork belly</strong> to a baking tray, fat-side down and keep the pan for later</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 35-45 min or until the pork belly is cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Tip: to check the pork is cooked, carefully pierce the thickest part with a sharp knife and, if it goes in easily, it's good to go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>parsnips</strong> (skins on) into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>apple<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[s]</span></strong> (skins on)&nbsp;into bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add both to a pot and cover with <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until they're fork-tender&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once tender, drain and return them to the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate the <strong>spring greens leaves</strong>, discarding any tough stalks</p>\r\n<p>Layer the leaves over eachother, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>Peel and roughly chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked and drained, mash the parnips and apple with 15g<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[30g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> and a splash of<strong> milk</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mash and season generously with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Set aside, covered, to keep warm until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span><strong>&nbsp;butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>spring greens</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>cold water</strong> and cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min, or until tender</p>\r\n<p>Once tender, season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and keep covered until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked through, transfer the <strong>pork belly</strong> to a clean chopping board</p>\r\n<p>Lay a tea towel over it and set aside for 5 min to rest</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/454_step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat the mash and spring greens&nbsp;through if they've gone cold before serving!</p>\r\n<p>Once rested, slice the pork belly thinly with a sharp knife</p>\r\n<p>Serve&nbsp;the sliced pork over the mash with any resting juices spooned over and the&nbsp;spring greens&nbsp;to the side&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
